Preheat your #oven{} to 180°C. Put a splash of oil in a large ovenproof pan on
medium heat. When hot, add the @Toulouse sausages{8} and brown all over, turning
frequently, ~{10%mins}.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal frying pan and then
> transfer to an ovenproof dish before your stew goes under the grill.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1} into half moons. Peel and grate
the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a garlic press). Drain the @cannellini beans{2}
in a #colander{} and rinse under cold water. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60@g} into a #small bowl{} and add the @panko breadcrumbs{50}. Season with
@black pepper{} and set aside. Slice the @goat's cheese{1} into eight rounds.

Halve the @ciabatta{2} lengthways and put on a #baking tray{}, cut-side up. Put
half the garlic in another small bowl and add the @olive oil{3}. Season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}. Mix well, then spoon over the cut-side of the
ciabatta. Pop your baking tray on the top shelf of your oven and bake for
~{12%mins}. When done, remove from the oven and wrap in #foil{} to keep warm.

When the sausages are nicely browned, add the onion to the pan and cook until
soft, ~{3%mins}. Add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Next,
add the @chicken stock pot{1}, @tomato passata{2} and cannellini beans. Pour in
the @water{200}, stir to combine and simmer until reduced by half, about
~{10%mins}.

Preheat your #grill{} to high. When the sauce in your stew has reduced by half
and is nice and thick, stir in the @baby spinach{1} and cook until completely
wilted, ~{2%mins}. Check the seasoning and add some @salt{} and @black pepper{}
if you like.

Remove your sausage stew from the heat (if you need to transfer it to an
#ovenproof dish{}, do so now) and lay the goat's cheese slices on top. Season
with black pepper.

> TIP: If the children don't like goat's cheese, leave it off one side.

Sprinkle over the cheesy breadcrumbs, then pop under the grill until the top is
golden brown and crunchy, ~{2-3%mins}. Serve in deep #bowls{} with a side of
garlic ciabatta. Bon appétit!